### What is the Bin Packing Problem?
The bin packing problem is a well-known problem in computer science. The goal is to pack a set of items of various sizes into the minimum number of bins of fixed capacity. In this case, the bins have a fixed capacity, and items are to be assigned to bins without exceeding their capacity.

### Heuristics:
Heuristics for bin packing include first-fit, best-fit, worst-fit, etc. These heuristics are used to determine which bin to place the next item into. The priority function here is used to compute a priority score for each bin, which is used to determine the order in which bins are considered when placing items.

