- Bins with lower variance in their current items have lower priority.

- Bins that can fit the item and have the least remaining space have higher priority.

- Bins that can fit the item and have the most remaining space have higher priority.

- Bins that can fit the item and have a certain ratio of remaining space to item size have higher priority.

